bilingual.source: It's not my face. It's my tooth.
bilingual.target: 不是我的脸，是我的牙齿。

bilingual.source: After I fill a tooth, my tooth feels much better.
bilingual.target: 补牙后，我的牙齿感觉好多了。
牙齿疼痛让他无法入睡。

bilingual.source: She needs to fill the cavity in her tooth.
bilingual.target: 她需要填补牙齿的空洞。

bilingual.source: The root canal treatment saved my tooth.
bilingual.target: 根管治疗拯救了我的牙齿。

list.abstract: tooth（英 [tuːθ]，美 [tuːθ]），英语单词，作名词为牙；齿；齿状物。短语搭配有tooth brush。例句为Tooth brushing became popular during the World War I.（刷牙在第一次世界大战期间变得流行。） 近义词有engage。

yingyinNormal.en: If you put the tooth under your pillow tonight, the Tooth Fairy will come. The Tooth Fairy will take the tooth. And in its place, she will leave a shiny coin.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你把牙齿放在你的枕头下面，牙仙子就会来找你，牙仙子会把牙齿拿走，在原来的位置上，她会留下一枚闪亮的金币。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Peppa. Would you like this coin in return for your tooth? What a nice, clean tooth. Thank you, Peppa, Goodnight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好啊，佩琪，你想要用你的牙齿换这枚闪亮的金币吗？真是一颗干净的牙齿，谢谢你佩琪，晚安。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa cannot wait to get into bed. Peppa is putting her tooth under the pillow for the Tooth Fairy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩琪迫不及待地去睡觉了。佩琪把牙齿放在枕头下面，等着牙仙子。

yingyinNormal.en: My money's on some kind of cult, the tooth, the long hair.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打赌肯定是什么邪教组织，牙齿，长头发。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. It's my tooth. It's fallen out. Don't worry, Peppa. It's just a milk tooth. They're meant to fall out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢。这是我的牙齿，可它掉下来了。别担心，佩琪，这只是一颗乳牙，就是要掉下来的。

yingyinNormal.en: What's that? It's a tooth. Where did that come from? Peppa, maybe you should look in the mirror.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么？这是一颗牙齿。那它是从哪里来的？佩琪，你该找个镜子照照。

yingyinNormal.en: He won't. You got Bad Tooth?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他不会的，你带着我的蛀牙吗？

yingyinNormal.en: The Tooth Fairy has arrived. But Peppa is asleep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这时牙仙子来了，但是佩琪睡着了。

yingyinNormal.en: The Tooth Fairy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 牙仙子。

yingyinNormal.en: This Tooth Fairy is very late. The Tooth Fairy is taking a long time to arrive. Where is that Tooth Fairy?
yingyinNormal.zh: 牙仙子来得也太晚了，牙仙子过了很久很久还是没来。牙仙子到底在哪里啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Will I grow a new one, Mummy? Yes, you will, Peppa. It also means the Tooth Fairy will be paying you a visit. Tooth Fairy? Yes, the Tooth Fairy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那会长一颗新牙出来吗？是的 你会长出一颗新牙的。掉牙也意味着牙仙子会过来看你的。牙仙子？是的。牙仙子。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa, what are you doing? I'm brushing my tooth so it is nice and clean for the Tooth Fairy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩琪，你在干什么？我在刷牙，牙仙子拿走的时候，会觉得它很干净。

yingyinNormal.en: To have Buddha on our side is a great ally, I know this. But as the Bible says, "An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth."
yingyinNormal.zh: 有佛教仁慈之心是好事，我知道，但《圣经》有云"以牙还牙 以眼还眼"。

yingyinNormal.en: Did the Tooth Fairy come? No. Let's take a look under your pillow. Look, Peppa. The Tooth Fairy has been and she's left you a coin. Hurray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 牙仙子来过了吗？没有。我们来看看你的枕头底下。看，佩琪，牙仙子已经来过了，还给你留了一枚金币。好诶。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, yeah, that is not quite right. And it hit my dead tooth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 味道是不太对，还弄疼我的烂牙了。

yingyinNormal.en: That's one way to pull a tooth. Huh. Darn kids. Good thing I...
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是拔牙的唯一方法，该死的小家伙。好消息是...

yingyinNormal.en: Quick, George, it's bedtime. We don't want to miss the Tooth Fairy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 快点，乔治，该睡觉了，我们可不想错过牙仙子。

yingyinNormal.en: And is there dental? 'cause I got a dead tooth doing nothing for me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 包括看牙医吗？因为我有颗没用的烂牙。

yingyinNormal.en: My meeting with the NRA did not go well. They're going to fight this tooth and nail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我跟全国步枪协会的见面并不顺利，他们打算全力以赴地阻挠此事。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, got it. Maybe you should just get Bluetooth. Okay. Blue Tooth, come over here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 明白了，也许你应该用蓝牙耳机。好吧，蓝牙，给我过来。

examination_example.sentence: Some groups would get each other's attention by rapping branches with their knuckles (指关节)，while others did it by loudly ripping leaves with their <highlight>teeth</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些小组会用指关节敲打树枝来吸引对方的注意，而另一些小组则用牙齿大声撕扯树叶。

examination_example.sentence: They found that the average person's mind wandered most frequently during personal activities, such as brushing their <highlight>teeth</highlight> and combing their hair.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们发现，一般人在做个人活动时走神的频率最高，比如刷牙和梳头。

examination_example.sentence: A pilot from Virginia removed his son's loose <highlight>tooth</highlight> using a helicopter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一名来自弗吉尼亚州的飞行员用直升机为他儿子拔掉了松动的牙齿。

examination_example.sentence: Instead, Mr Rahim tied one end of a string around his son's <highlight>tooth</highlight>, and the other end to his full-sized commercial helicopter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，拉希姆先生将绳子的一端系在儿子的牙齿上，另一端系在他的全尺寸的商用直升机上。

examination_example.sentence: Most important of all, avoid giving ants any access to food, particularly sugary food, because ants have a sweet <highlight>tooth</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最重要的是，不要让蚂蚁接触任何食物，尤其是含糖的食物，因为蚂蚁喜欢吃甜食。
